@mirjak  I agree that having a signal for stand-by is beneficial. Actually, we did have the standy-by signal with the PATH_STATUS frame in draft-liu. The PATH_STATUS frame signals three status: (1) abandon, (2) stand-by, and (3) available. 
     PATH_STATUS Frame {
       Type (i) = TBD-03 (experiments use 0xbaba03),
       Path Identifier (..),
       Path Status sequence number (i),
       Path Status (i),
       Path Priority (i),
     }
When the three drafts were merged, the PATH_STATUS frame was replaced by the current PATH_ABANDON frame, as at that time we wanted the first version to focus on the very basic features. I think we can put the stand-by status back if it proves to be a general requirement.

